{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 50,
  "title": "第五十章（生死）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "出生，入死。"
    },
    {
      "text": "生之徒十有三。"
    },
    {
      "text": "死之徒十有三。"
    },
    {
      "text": "而民生生。"
    },
    {
      "text": "動皆之死地之十有三"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫何故也？"
    },
    {
      "text": "以亓生生也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "蓋聞善攝生者："
    },
    {
      "text": "陵行不辟兕虎。"
    },
    {
      "text": "入軍不被甲兵。"
    },
    {
      "text": "兕无所椯亓角。"
    },
    {
      "text": "虎无所措亓爪。"
    },
    {
      "text": "兵无所容亓刃。"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫何故也？"
    },
    {
      "text": "以亓无死地焉。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "出生，謂情欲出五內，魂靜魄定，故生。入死，謂情欲入於胸臆，精勞神惑，故死。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言生死之類各有十三，謂九竅四關也。其生也目不妄視，耳不妄聽，鼻不妄香臭，口不妄言味，手不妄持，足不妄行，精神不妄施。其死也反是也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人知求生，動作反之十三死也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "問何故動之死地也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "所以動之死地者，以其求生活之事太厚，違道忤天，妄行失紀。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "攝，養也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "自然遠離，害不干也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不好戰以殺人。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 12,
          "start": 7,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "養生之人，兕虎無由傷，兵刃無從加之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "問兕虎兵甲何故不加害之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以其不犯十三之死地也。言神明營護之，此物不敢害。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "出生地，入死地。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 9,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "十有三，猶云十分有三分，取其生道，全生之極，十分有三耳。取死之道，全死之極，亦十分有三耳。而民生生之厚，更之無生之地焉，善攝生者無以生為 生，故無死地也。器之害者，莫甚乎兵戈，獸之害者，莫甚乎兕虎，而令兵戈無所容其鋒刃，虎兕無所措其爪角，斯誠不以欲累其身者也，何死地之有乎。夫蚖蟺以 淵為淺，而鑿穴其中，鷹鸇以山為卑，而增巢其上，矰繳不能及，網罟不能到，可謂處於無死地矣，然而卒以甘餌，乃入於無生之地，豈非生生之厚乎，故物茍不以 求離其本，不以欲渝其真，雖入軍而不害，陸行而不可犯也，赤子之可則而貴信矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
